{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 03:33:47.818576", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- The SDN spine–leaf network is experiencing a complete data-plane outage. No host-to-host connectivity is working, including between hosts on the same leaf switch.\\n\\nKey Findings and Evidence\\n1) End-host connectivity failures\\n- host_1_1 → host_1_2 (same leaf, same subnet): 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.1.\\n- host_1_1 → host_2_1 (across leaves): 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\n- host_2_1 → host_2_2 (same leaf): 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\n- Host interfaces are up with valid 10.0.0.0/24 addresses; RX packet counters remain at 0, indicating frames are not reaching the hosts.\\n\\n2) Open vSwitch (OVS) control-plane status\\n- All OVS bridges (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are configured for Controller “tcp:20.0.0.100:6633” with fail_mode: secure.\\n- All report is_connected=false and status: last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF.\\n- Flow tables on all switches are empty (ovs-ofctl dump-flows shows only header), so unmatched traffic is dropped.\\n\\n3) Management-plane connectivity to controller IP\\n- From leaf_1, ping to 20.0.0.100 succeeds (0% loss). This confirms L3 management reachability is fine; the refusal is at the TCP service level on 20.0.0.100:6633, not a network reachability issue.\\n\\nAnomaly Detection\\n- Severe anomaly: The SDN controller service at 20.0.0.100 is refusing OpenFlow connections on port 6633. With fail_mode set to secure and no controller session established, OVS does not perform L2 learning or forwarding, so all data traffic (including ARP) is dropped.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Primary faulty component: SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 (controller process/port).\\n- Affected devices: leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 (all OVS instances), which are operating in secure mode without flow programming.\\n- Hosts are not directly at fault (interfaces up, correct IPs), but are impacted because their traffic is dropped by the switches.\\n\\nProbable Root Cause\\n- The OpenFlow controller is not listening on TCP 6633 (or is actively rejecting), or there is a port mismatch (switches expect 6633 while the controller listens on a different port, e.g., 6653). Consequently, no flows are installed and all switches drop traffic due to secure mode.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- Entire data-plane outage across the fabric:\\n  - Intra-leaf L2 communication fails (no ARP/ICMP).\\n  - Inter-leaf communication fails.\\n  - Control-plane reachability to controller IP is OK, but the OpenFlow session cannot be established, so the fabric is non-functional for tenant traffic., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='bf6167a1-0505-4739-8757-e674c581cc75'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
